CSO is "Central Sign On", an application supports LDAP and OpenID.

LDAP server             <-- LDAP --> CSO <-- OpenID --> Other applications
(Active Directory etc.)

== Install

Requirements:
* Ruby 1.8.7, because ruby-openid does not work with Ruby 1.9.2
* Rails 3

Copy config/cso.rb.sample to config/cso.rb, and to fit your environment.

Then run as a normal Rails application.
